<TITLE> Road accident kills 8 in Sirajganj </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Sirajganj, April 24 (bdnews24.com) At least eight people died and six others were injured when a loaded truck rammed into another lorry parked on the roadside in Sirajganj Wednesday night, police said Both tumbled into a roadside ditch near Daatpur bridge under Raiganj upazila of the district, Tozammel Hossain, officer-in-charge of Hatikumrul Highway Police Station, told bdnews24.com Thursday. The accident occurred around 11:45pm Wednesday when a Dhaka-bound truck carrying tomatoes veered out of control and slammed into another truck loaded with hay. Seven people travelling aboard the trucks died on the scene. One of the injured died on his way to hospital. The dead are Lal Miah, 35, of Dariapur under Shahjadpur upazila in Sirajganj, Rahimuddin, 50, a hay trader from Kakalbari village, Ershad Ali, 30, Rezaul, 25, Ratan, 20, Jahangir, 35, Moslem, 22, and tomato trader Faizer Sarkar, 60, from Shariatpur. The injured were admitted to Sirajganj Sadar Hospital. bdnews24.com/
